content:
import seaborn as sns
from faicons import icon_svg

# Import data from shared.py
from shared import app_dir, df

from shiny import reactive
from shiny.express import input, render, ui

ui.page_opts(title="Property dashboard", fillable=True)


with ui.sidebar(title="Filter controls"):
    ui.input_slider("Price", "Price", 2000, 18000000, 1800000, step=1000)
    ui.input_checkbox_group(
        "City",
        "City",
        ['Joshua Tree', 'Panorama Heights', 'Yucca Valley', 'Big Bear City',
       'Big Bear Lake'],
        selected=['Joshua Tree', 'Panorama Heights', 'Yucca Valley', 'Big Bear City',
       'Big Bear Lake'],
    )
    ui.input_checkbox_group(
        "Pool",
        "Pool",
        [True],
        selected=['True'],
    )


with ui.layout_column_wrap(fill=False):
    with ui.value_box(showcase=icon_svg("house")):
        "Number of Properties"

        @render.text
        def count():
            return filtered_df().shape[0]

    with ui.value_box(showcase=icon_svg("ruler-horizontal")):
        "Average Price"

        @render.text
        def bill_length():
            return f"${filtered_df()['Price'].mean():.1f}"

    with ui.value_box(showcase=icon_svg("dollar-sign")):
        "Rent Estimate"

        @render.text
        def bill_depth():
            return f"{filtered_df()['Rent Estimate'].mean():.1f} mm"


with ui.layout_columns():
    with ui.card(full_screen=True):
        ui.card_header("Bill length and depth")

        @render.plot
        def length_depth():
            return sns.scatterplot(
                data=filtered_df(),
                x="Price",
                y="Rent Estimate",
                hue="City",
            )

    with ui.card(full_screen=True):
        ui.card_header("Property data")

        @render.data_frame
        def summary_statistics():
            cols = [
                "Price",
                "City",
                "Rent Estimate",
            ]
            return render.DataGrid(filtered_df()[cols], filters=True)

with ui.layout_columns():
    with ui.card(full_screen=True):
        ui.card_header("Bill length and depth")

        @render.plot
        def leng_depth():
            return sns.boxplot(
                data=filtered_df(),
                x="City",
                y="Rent Estimate",
            )


ui.include_css(app_dir / "styles.css")


@reactive.calc
def filtered_df():
    filt_df = df[df["City"].isin(input.City())]
    filt_df = filt_df.loc[filt_df["Price"] < input.Price()]
    if input.Pool():
        filt_df = df[df["Pool"]==True]
    return filt_df
